snippet.textDisplay: I been to Egypt few times but then realised it's indeed a dangerous place to visit for so many reason from food safety to security to disease called heptititis C which is widely spread amongst modern Egyptian. I also know a couple of my friends who came back  to Moscow with virus C that attacks the liver tissue. It's a fatal disease transmitted through so many aspects one of them being through contaminated food and water. I recommend you get vaccinated before making your journey to Egypt. If you've to visit Egypt though you can go to Aswan city where ancient  Egypt black  Nubian (Egyptian indigenous) are presented. It's a bit cleaner than the rest of Egypt.

snippet.textDisplay: Totally sucks when ur getting scammed but I'm glad you posted this video. It's an important lesson, and part of the travelling experience. Scammers operate in so many countries taking advantage of guests to their country. A scourge to society, and an object of shame to their own people. For some reason they often come in the form of taxi drivers and tour operators. Sounds like you handled it well though. I learnt the hard way to never let someone touch your wallet or phone to "help" you.
